keywords.description:
Both items must evaluate true.
Same as: &&
if (x AND y)
if (x && y)

Check if item is of a certain class type, such as number, string, object, or array.
Same as using: if (Type() = "TypeName")
if (var IS Number)
if (my_arr is Array)
if !(item IS object)

One item OR the other must bet true.
Same as: ||
if (var1 OR var2)
if (var1 OR !var2)

Creates a decision branch. When the supplied expression evaluates as true, the following code block is executed.
if (1 = 1)
if (var1 = var2)

